												<div class="description author withsidebar">
													<h6><a href="https://lithub.com/author/jeanmartinbauer/">Jean-Martin Bauer</a></h6>
													Jean-Martin Bauer has served with the World Food Programme in the Sahel and central Africa and has responded to food emergencies in Afghanistan and Syria. Bauer has led WFP country offices in the Republic of the Congo and in Haiti. His work has also focused on leveraging digital tech and analytics to fight hunger. A Washington, DC, native, Bauer holds degrees from the London School of Economics and the Harvard Kennedy School.																									</div>
